id: pm-owm0
title: "SDK testing helper to invoke a registered extension command handler: runRegisteredCommandForTest"
description: "Complete the package-author testing loop. The SDK testing surface can assert registrations exist (assertRegistered*), activate (activateExtensionForTest), and deactivate (deactivateExtensionForTest), but offers no supported way to INVOKE a registered command handler and assert its behavior. Authors must hand-construct a CommandHandlerContext and reach for the internal runCommandHandler. Add runRegisteredCommandForTest(commands, { command, args, options, global, pmRoot }) that builds the context with agent-safe defaults (json+quiet+noPager), throws a descriptive error listing available handlers when the command is unregistered (a wiring/typo bug), and otherwise returns the real CommandHandlerResult so authors can assert .result/.handled/.errorMessage. Because registerImporter/registerExporter create '<name> import'/'<name> export' command paths, the same helper exercises importers/exporters too. Wire an invoke step into the package scaffold sample test and document in SDK + package authoring guides."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk","area:testing",context-management
created_at: "2026-06-21T13:24:57.908Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-21T13:42:14.191Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Added runRegisteredCommandForTest(commands, options) to src/sdk/testing.ts, re-exported it (and CommandHandlerResult) from the sdk + sdk/testing barrels, wired an invoke step into the package scaffold sample test, and documented it in SDK.md + EXTENSIONS.md."
expected_result: "Package authors can invoke a registered command/importer/exporter handler through the public SDK and assert its CommandHandlerResult, completing the activate -> assert -> run -> deactivate testing loop."
actual_result: Helper ships at 100% coverage (4809 tests green); a freshly scaffolded package's generated node --test run passes the new invoke assertions end-to-end against the built SDK.
