learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-21T13:42:04.218Z",claude-code-agent,"runRegisteredCommandForTest takes activation.commands (ExtensionCommandRegistry), mirroring assertRegisteredCommandOverride and the internal runCommandHandler, NOT activation.registrations (which the contract/metadata asserts use). Distinguishes the two handled:false runtime cases: no matching handler is a test wiring bug so the helper PRE-CHECKS and throws with the available-handlers list, while a handler that throws a non-exit error returns {handled:false,errorMessage} for the caller to assert; an error carrying numeric exitCode propagates (matches runtime). The [...options.args] spread is required (readonly string[] -> mutable string[] + undefined default), not merely defensive. Importers/exporters are covered for free because registerImporter/registerExporter create \"<name> import\"/\"<name> export\" handler paths. CommandHandlerResult had to be added to the SDK index type re-exports so authors can type the return value."
